      "message": "\u003e Done. I have updated the Signed-off-by line with my full name, which serves as my DCO/CLA agreement.\n\nThat\u0027s not how this works.  OpenBMC does not use DCO; it uses CLAs.\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#starting-out\n\nIf you are doing work on behalf of your company or your company is engaged in BMC-like software development, we require you to get a CCLA from your company.\n\nIf you are doing work purely on a hobbyist path, you can sign an ICLA, but you\u0027ll likely be asked to justify why that is appropriate for your work.\n\nIn the meantime, thank you for pointing out the bad URL.  I\u0027ve updated the file to include a correct URL:\n\nremote:   https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/91521 rest-api: update URL [NEW]\n\nIf you want to continue to propose a change to use MDN documentation instead, please get on a CLA.",
